title: US, Japanese Leaders Deliver Joint Statement After North Korea Missile Launch
text:
US, Japanese Leaders Deliver Joint Statement After North Korea Missile Launch Â© AP Photo/ Pablo Martinez Monsivais 0 29 0 0 Donald Trump and Shinzo Abe have delivered an unscheduled joint brief statement. 
US President Donald Trump and Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe have delivered an unscheduled joint brief statement after North Korean missile launch. 
The Prime Minister of Japan has called DPRK's ballistic missile launch "absolutely intolerable". He also said that he had agreed with Trump to enforce US-Japanese alliance. ...
